
TO INSTALL:

cd ~
git clone http://github.com/jbe/.vim.git
ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc
cd ~/.vim
git submodule init
git submodule update


FEATURES

* My opinions

* Syntax support
  - Markdown (and markdown-preview)
  - CoffeeScript
  - Slim templates

* Integration
  - Git (fugitive.vim)
  - Jekyll blogging (jekyll.vim)
  - Wordpress blogging (blogit.vim)
  - Hithub gists (gist.vim)

* Useful plugins
  - NERDTree
  - Taglist
  - Tab completion (snipmate.vim)


REQUIREMENTS

Exuberant ctags (for taglist)
$ sudo apt-get install ctags

Pandoc (for wordpress integration)
$ sudo apt-get install pandoc


BLOGGING TO WORDPRESS

$ cp passwords.vim.template passwords.vim
$ vim passwords.vim

Make sure ruby and pandoc is installed. Wordpress timezone settings might prevent your posts from being immediately released.

I am using two wrapper scripts to enable syntax highlighting. If you use the following syntax, it should be highlighted on wordpress.com:

[code ruby]

  def time
    :now
  end

[end]


TIPS

Have a look at the key bindings in vimrc for some inspiration.

Do :BundleInstall to update the plugins at any time :)
